article.headline: Albany, NY 78, Cornell 75
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Brian Lillis scored five unanswered points late in the game, rallying Albany to a 78-75 victory over Cornell on Friday night. Louis Dale made a 3-pointer to give Cornell (4-6) its last lead at 68-66. Then Albany (6-4) came down the floor and gave the ball to Lillis who scored a layup while drawing a foul from Dale with 3:28 left. Lillis made the free throw to give the Great Danes a 69-68 edge. Lillis made two more free throws with 2:38 remaining as Albany stretched its lead to 71-68. The Great Danes eventually led by four, before Dale hit a 3-pointer with 11 seconds left to cut Albany's lead to 76-75. Jamar Wilson sank two free throws for the game's final points and a 3-point shot by Dale fell short. Brent Wilson lead Albany with 19 points. Dale scored a game-high 22 points and teammate Ryan Wittman added 20 for the Big Red. The Great Danes shot 63.6 percent from the floor (14-of-22) after halftime.
